@{ Layout = null; }
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Dancing+Script&family=Inter:wght@300;400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/skolar-dialog.css">
    <title>Tutor Terms and Conditions | Skolar</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="./assets/img/skolarlogo.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/main-css/terms.css">
</head>
<body>
    <script src="~/js/skolar-dialog.js"></script>

    <main class="terms-page">
        <section class="terms-card">

            <p class="terms-label">SKOLAR PLATFORM</p>
            <h1>Terms and Conditions for Tutors</h1>
            <p class="updated-text">Effective Date: June 2026 | Version 1.1</p>

            <div class="terms-content">
                <p>
                    Welcome to Skolar. By registering an account as an independent educator on our platform,
                    you accept and agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. These rules are put in
                    place to ensure a professional, secure, and reliable learning marketplace for both tutors
                    and students.
                </p>

                <h2>1. Eligibility and Mandatory Identity Verification</h2>
                <p>
                    To preserve platform security, all tutors must pass an identity validation check before
                    conducting sessions or receiving payouts.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Valid Government ID:</strong> You are required to upload a legible, unexpired
                        government-issued photo ID, such as a passport, driver's license, or national ID,
                        during registration.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Data Encryption:</strong> Your identity documents are encrypted and securely
                        stored by Skolar Administration for safety verification and tracking. They are never
                        shared with or made visible to students.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Account Accountability:</strong> You may only operate under your legal name.
                        Profile misrepresentation, impersonation, or permitting third parties to use your
                        account will result in immediate termination.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>2. Platform Operational Standards</h2>
                <p>
                    Skolar regulates basic operational formats to align user expectations and optimize
                    academic outcomes.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Minimum Session Duration:</strong> To provide substantial and structured
                        academic support, all scheduled tutoring sessions must be a minimum of one (1) hour
                        in duration. Sessions cannot be broken up into shorter intervals or truncated
                        post-booking.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Independent Contractor Status:</strong> Tutors operate as independent service
                        providers. You set your availability and choose your clients within platform guidelines,
                        but must adhere strictly to the schedule you commit to.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>3. Cancellation and Penalty Policy</h2>
                <p>
                    When a session is confirmed, a student reserves their time and allocates funds.
                    Last-minute cancellations disrupt their education significantly. As such, Skolar enforces
                    strict penalties for late cancellations by tutors:
                </p>

                <div class="terms-table-wrap">
                    <table class="terms-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Cancellation Timeline</th>
                                <th>Impact on Student</th>
                                <th>Penalty Enforced on Tutor</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>

                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>2+ Days Before Session</strong><br>
                                    <span>More than 48 hours notice</span>
                                </td>
                                <td>100% refund of the affected session fee.</td>
                                <td>No warning, financial fine, or discount credit is issued.</td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>Day-Before Cancellation</strong><br>
                                    <span>24 to 48 hours notice</span>
                                </td>
                                <td>100% refund of the affected session fee.</td>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>1 official warning</strong> recorded against your account history.
                                </td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>Same-Day Cancellation</strong><br>
                                    <span>Less than 24 hours notice</span>
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    100% refund of session fee.<br>
                                    <strong>+ 20% discount credit</strong> applied to their next 2-hour booking.
                                </td>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>20% financial fine</strong> calculated from your next completed
                                    session's gross earnings.
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h3>3.1 Progressive Disciplinary & Escalation Track</h3>
                <p>
                    Skolar monitors cancellation history to protect platform integrity. Repeated scheduling
                    failures lead to the following consequences:
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Account Suspension:</strong> Accumulating three (3) official warnings for
                        day-before cancellations triggers an automatic one-week or seven-day suspension from
                        the marketplace, preventing new bookings or visibility.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Permanent Account Ban:</strong> Skolar enforces a strict three-strike major
                        policy. If a tutor reaches their third major disciplinary action, they will be permanently
                        banned from the platform with forfeiture of pending platform bonuses.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <h3>⚠ Anti-Circumvention Rule</h3>
                    <p>
                        To protect payment processing and platform security, all interactions, scheduling
                        updates, and financial transactions must happen exclusively within Skolar. Soliciting
                        students for external payments or sharing personal contact details to bypass platform
                        fees will cause immediate, permanent termination of your account.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2>4. Payment, Refund, and Payout Processing</h2>
                <p>
                    Skolar is designed to connect to an authorized third-party payment provider for checkout,
                    refund, learner credit, tutor compensation, and payout processing. Sensitive payment credentials
                    must be handled by the connected provider and must not be stored by Skolar.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Gross session amount:</strong> tutor hourly rate × session duration.</li>
                    <li>Learner cancellations may retain part of the paid session amount as tutor compensation.</li>
                    <li>Same-day tutor cancellation creates a 20% learner voucher and a pending fine equal to 20% of the tutor's next completed session gross earnings.</li>
                    <li>Payment, refund, and payout records update after the connected provider confirms the result.</li>
                    <li>For date-range bookings, every session is calculated and refunded independently.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>5. Exclusive Administrative Review</h2>
                <p>
                    Any disputes, billing inquiries, student complaints, or cancellation appeal requests must
                    be submitted exclusively to the Skolar Administration through official Help Center channels.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Tutors agree to submit to the findings and mediation of the administrative team.</li>
                    <li>
                        Users agree not to pursue external legal or public disputes before allowing the
                        administrative review process to conclude. All decisions rendered by Skolar
                        Administration regarding refunds, fine assessments, suspensions, or bans are final
                        and contractually binding.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>6. Academic Integrity & Code of Conduct</h2>
                <p>
                    Skolar is built to facilitate educational growth, not shortcuts. Tutors must abide by strict
                    ethical academic boundaries.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Prohibited Assistance:</strong> You are strictly forbidden from directly
                        completing exams, writing essays, or executing graded assignments for a student.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Educational Scope:</strong> Your duty is to guide, explain concepts, mentor,
                        and teach. Direct completion of graded student material constitutes academic
                        dishonesty and will result in a permanent ban under a zero-tolerance policy.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Professionalism:</strong> You must maintain an appropriate, respectful, and
                        strictly professional demeanor during all video and messaging interactions.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>7. Limitation of Liability and Indemnification</h2>
                <p>
                    Skolar provides the marketplace infrastructure connecting students and tutors but does
                    not employ the tutors. Skolar is not liable for personal conduct, grade outcomes, or any
                    off-platform interactions. Tutors agree to indemnify and hold harmless Skolar against any
                    claims resulting from their individual actions or tutoring services.
                </p>
            </div>

            <a href="@Url.Action("Signup", "Home")?role=tutor" class="agree-btn">Back to Tutor Sign Up</a>
        </section>
    </main>

</body>
</html>
